1
00:00:43,060 --> 00:00:46,780
=Auspicious Nobles=

2
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:49,940
=Episode 7=

3
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:52,500
(The Crown Prince's Ways of Wooing)

4
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:56,970
Since the rice balls aren't selling,

5
00:00:57,030 --> 00:00:58,580
we must find another way to make money.

6
00:00:59,070 --> 00:01:01,520
It's not that there's a problem
with my rice balls.

7
00:01:01,530 --> 00:01:03,990
It's because the Inspectorate
is keeping too close a tab on us.

8
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:08,070
We have to go to Yuanzhao.

9
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:09,280
Get him to sell them?

10
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:12,120
To open the shop under his name.

11
00:01:13,230 --> 00:01:15,120
Even if Zheng Yuanhe despises him,

12
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,480
openly,

13
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:18,400
he can't possibly
trash his own brother's shop.

14
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:22,200
Although we'll have
to give him a 20 percent cut,

15
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:23,870
and the closer we get to him,

16
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:24,870
the more hostility

17
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,680
we will draw from Zheng Yuanhe,

18
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,280
we don't have a choice right now.

19
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:31,000
Let's just survive this month first.

20
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:32,920
Tomorrow, I'll have
Caiyuan go look for...

21
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,000
No.

22
00:01:38,510 --> 00:01:41,400
Tomorrow, we are going
to Yuanzhao's residence.

23
00:01:43,140 --> 00:01:44,420
(Zhao Prince's Residence)

24
00:01:44,430 --> 00:01:45,480
Tower Master?

25
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:46,680
Are you sure you didn't mistake her?

26
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:48,300
I wouldn't dare
lie to you, Your Highness.

27
00:01:48,310 --> 00:01:49,910
I saw them the moment
I opened the door this morning,

28
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:51,430
so I quickly brought them
to the guest room.

29
00:01:51,430 --> 00:01:52,200
Don't worry.

30
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:54,030
I've already instructed
everyone in the residence

31
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:55,000
not to talk out of line.

32
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:57,200
Jiang Shuo,

33
00:01:57,350 --> 00:01:58,430
just wait outside.

34
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,070
And then...

35
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:05,840
Yes, Your Highness.

36
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:15,280
Tower Master,

37
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:17,510
I thought Wangshi Tower
didn't want me anymore.

38
00:02:17,910 --> 00:02:18,710
These past few days,

39
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:19,710
you have no idea how much I missed...

40
00:02:19,710 --> 00:02:20,190
Shut up.

41
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:25,240
You made such a big fuss to find me

42
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,670
and even looked
all the way to the Pan Residence.

43
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:32,240
Are you trying to test if Wangshi Tower
still holds its power?

44
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:34,100
No, it's not like that.

45
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:35,190
Tower Master,

46
00:02:35,260 --> 00:02:36,630
wasn't it because I hadn't received

47
00:02:36,630 --> 00:02:38,000
your brilliant master plan yet?

48
00:02:38,010 --> 00:02:39,400
I've been scratching my head every day.

49
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,710
I was anxious, you know?

50
00:02:40,710 --> 00:02:42,290
The Wangshi Tower stronghold was raided,

51
00:02:42,510 --> 00:02:44,280
yet you're only thinking
about making money?

52
00:02:44,590 --> 00:02:45,310
No...

53
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:45,920
Tower Master,

54
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,120
you are so deeply shrewd...

55
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:49,630
I mean, wise and brilliant.

56
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:52,470
My older brother's petty tricks
won't trouble you.

57
00:02:52,910 --> 00:02:55,680
This comes from
my trust in your capabilities.

58
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:56,840
Annoying.

59
00:02:59,710 --> 00:03:00,520
Give it to him.

60
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:05,900
(Master Plan)

61
00:03:06,710 --> 00:03:08,400
So this is the master plan.

62
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:13,750
Commander Jiu,

63
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,120
please slow down.

64
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,060
(Master Plan:
Rice Balls for Wealth and Prosperity)

65
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:17,830
Selling rice balls?

66
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:23,000
(It really is Miss Qingqing.)

67
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,030
Who goes there?

68
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:27,840
Forget it.

69
00:03:34,310 --> 00:03:36,000
Since you're so interested

70
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,080
in my identity,

71
00:03:38,710 --> 00:03:40,520
then why should we beat around the bush?

72
00:03:42,590 --> 00:03:43,710
You dog.

73
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:45,200
How dare you offend the Tower Master?

74
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,470
Apologize to her now.

75
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:47,680
"Tower Master," you say?

76
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:50,630
Didn't you just see my face?

77
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:53,590
No, I didn't.

78
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:55,520
I was bowing down just now.

79
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,240
I just saw you

80
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:59,240
looking around with
those shifty eyes of yours.

81
00:03:59,870 --> 00:04:01,430
How dare you deny it?

82
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:02,560
Tower Master,

83
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,000
I have a terrible memory.

84
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:05,310
I can't remember faces at all.

85
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:06,800
Jiuzhu.

86
00:04:08,870 --> 00:04:09,430
Your Highness!

87
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:10,190
Don't come in.

88
00:04:11,590 --> 00:04:12,590
Don't be impulsive.

89
00:04:12,910 --> 00:04:14,310
We are tied to the same string...

90
00:04:15,230 --> 00:04:16,680
I mean, we are in the same boat now.

91
00:04:17,630 --> 00:04:20,120
You smooth-tongued, smart aleck.

92
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,200
If you dare utter any more nonsense,

93
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:23,920
I'll let you have a chat with Jiuzhu.

94
00:04:24,510 --> 00:04:25,430
Qingqing,

95
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:26,920
Tower Master,

96
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:30,390
I am of one mind with you.

97
00:04:32,430 --> 00:04:33,390
I swear,

98
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,600
I will never tell anyone your identity.

99
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:36,560
Otherwise,

100
00:04:36,870 --> 00:04:37,950
for the rest of my life,

101
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,630
every business I run will fail,

102
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:41,830
and whatever I sell will lose money.

103
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:43,430
As for this rice ball business,

104
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:45,870
you'll give an extra ten percent
to Wangshi Tower.

105
00:04:47,270 --> 00:04:48,270
Giving another cut?

106
00:04:48,270 --> 00:04:49,370
I'll only have ten percent left...

107
00:04:50,430 --> 00:04:50,950
I'll pay.

108
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:53,120
I'll definitely pay.

109
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:54,390
As long as you want it,

110
00:04:55,110 --> 00:04:56,270
I'll give as much as it takes.

111
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,920
Fine. Go get ready.

112
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:05,270
I'll open rice ball shops
all over the capital right away.

113
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:08,750
(What a massive loss)

114
00:05:09,330 --> 00:05:10,600
(glancing at the Tower Master.)

115
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:20,020
(Noble Rice Balls)

116
00:05:21,190 --> 00:05:24,040
Grand opening of Noble Rice Balls!

117
00:05:24,220 --> 00:05:25,120
Come on in, customers.

118
00:05:26,070 --> 00:05:27,040
Buy today,

119
00:05:27,190 --> 00:05:29,190
and get one free tomorrow
with your receipt stub.

120
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:30,240
Buy one, get one free?

121
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:31,560
Wow, there's such a good deal?

122
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:32,990
- Quick, let's go check it out.
- Let's go.

123
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,310
Buy one, get one free.

124
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:35,920
With your receipt stub,
buy one, get one free.

125
00:05:35,930 --> 00:05:36,510
Tomorrow, okay?

126
00:05:36,510 --> 00:05:37,600
- Remember to bring your receipt stub.
- I want one too.

127
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:38,830
Don't rush, there's enough for everyone.

128
00:05:38,830 --> 00:05:39,680
Please come inside. Inside.

129
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:42,480
See that? You still have to
rely on marketing strategies.

130
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:45,070
Although my heart is bleeding,

131
00:05:45,630 --> 00:05:47,190
once the popularity is here,

132
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:49,240
can the money be far behind?

133
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,160
Tower Master, you're brilliant.

134
00:05:51,630 --> 00:05:53,390
Now the brothers' pay for next month

135
00:05:53,390 --> 00:05:54,360
is taken care of.

136
00:05:56,980 --> 00:05:58,820
(Inspectorate)

137
00:06:06,270 --> 00:06:08,430
(My chance to move up
in the world has come.)

138
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:11,560
(The Crown Prince must want to put me
in an important position.)

139
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:13,950
(From now on, in this capital,)

140
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:18,160
(let's see who still dares
to look down on me!)

141
00:06:23,190 --> 00:06:23,630
This...

142
00:06:24,390 --> 00:06:25,390
Commander Chang.

143
00:06:26,630 --> 00:06:27,310
Lord Pan,

144
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,790
His Highness has
important matters to attend to.

145
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:31,070
Just wait here for now.

146
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,070
Yes,

147
00:06:32,070 --> 00:06:32,800
as it should be.

148
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:35,000
I shall respectfully await
His Highness here.

149
00:07:12,580 --> 00:07:14,140
(Crossbow)

150
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,100
(This scheming fool
sneaked in so late at night...)

151
00:07:27,230 --> 00:07:28,800
(He wouldn't be here to kill me, right?)

152
00:07:31,830 --> 00:07:32,510
Li Qingqing.

153
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,240
Your Highness.

154
00:07:41,830 --> 00:07:44,240
(Oh no. I'm so nervous.)

155
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:49,190
What brings Your Highness to grace
my small courtyard with your presence?

156
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,830
Do you recognize this object?

157
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:58,270
(How did this thing
end up in his hands?)

158
00:07:58,950 --> 00:08:00,600
During the Lantern Festival a year ago,

159
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:02,390
you saved me.

160
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,240
I

161
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,480
picked up this crossbow blueprint.

162
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:09,750
The design is ingenious,

163
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:11,750
so I came to ask for your insights.

164
00:08:14,860 --> 00:08:16,730
Your Highness has mistaken me
for someone else.

165
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:18,600
It's not mine.

166
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:20,310
(She refuses to admit it.)

167
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:23,000
(Could it be she's afraid of being
misunderstood by Pan Yang again?)

168
00:08:23,950 --> 00:08:25,560
(He doesn't look like he believes me.)

169
00:08:25,650 --> 00:08:27,860
(I'll just say some superficial stuff
to send him away first.)

170
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:33,360
Although this blueprint
was not drawn by me,

171
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:36,440
I do know a thing or two
about mechanical arts.

172
00:08:36,550 --> 00:08:38,600
I can help look it over for you,
Your Highness.

173
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:41,460
Sorry to trouble you.

174
00:08:44,870 --> 00:08:46,390
The designer of this blueprint

175
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,550
used an elastic mechanism
to replace the traditional bowstring,

176
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,520
allowing the bolts to shoot further.

177
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,440
Such a design is indeed ingenious.

178
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:56,000
However, the recoil will also increase.

179
00:08:56,550 --> 00:08:58,840
Ordinary wood would run
the risk of splitting.

180
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:01,120
(He actually does understand it.)

181
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,510
I have been wondering

182
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:06,080
exactly what material would be
more suitable for the crossbow body.

183
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,120
Why not try boxwood?

184
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:13,080
Boxwood has natural resilience
and does not split easily.

185
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:15,240
If you then soak it in tung oil,

186
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:16,470
it will be moisture-proof and durable.

187
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,600
It would work well this way.

188
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:18,910
However,

189
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:21,270
the bolt groove needs
to be polished smoother.

190
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,840
Otherwise, when it's fired,

191
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:23,840
it can easily get jammed.

192
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,030
You are indeed intelligent.

193
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:29,390
I'm just talking nonsense.

194
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,270
It's all nonsense.

195
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,270
If it actually works,

196
00:09:33,390 --> 00:09:34,550
it's purely a coincidence.

197
00:09:36,270 --> 00:09:37,000
True.

198
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:39,270
Talking on paper always lacks depth.

199
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,480
One still needs to test it hands-on

200
00:09:41,790 --> 00:09:43,550
to know whether it's feasible or not.

201
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,080
(What is he trying to do?)

202
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:21,670
How is it?

203
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:27,030
(I intentionally gave him
so many wrong steps,)

204
00:10:27,150 --> 00:10:28,750
(yet he actually managed to make it.)

205
00:10:29,390 --> 00:10:31,480
(He is natural material
to be a top artisan.)

206
00:10:32,550 --> 00:10:34,670
(What a pity he thinks
about killing me all day.)

207
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:37,060
(Otherwise, if I poached him
to be the technical director,)

208
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:38,540
(I would have made a fortune long ago.)

209
00:10:38,550 --> 00:10:39,200
This

210
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:42,120
is for you.

211
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:44,240
(Giving me a weapon?)

212
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,270
(What does this mean?)

213
00:10:45,390 --> 00:10:46,550
(Is he warning me?)

214
00:10:51,610 --> 00:10:52,870
Although this crossbow is small,

215
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:54,750
within three paces,

216
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,600
it can instantly kill someone.

217
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,150
(If Pan Yang bullies her again,)

218
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,290
(I hope she can put it to use.)

219
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:05,750
(The distance between us right now
isn't even three paces.)

220
00:11:09,030 --> 00:11:09,440
Thank...

221
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,080
Thank you for the reward, Your Highness.

222
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:14,630
I

223
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:17,030
will take good care of it.

224
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:19,840
I would never dare

225
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:22,000
to use it lightly.

226
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:27,750
You...

227
00:11:30,270 --> 00:11:31,480
Take care of yourself.

228
00:11:40,670 --> 00:11:43,080
He clearly came here
just to give me a blunt warning.

229
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:44,710
Your Highness,

230
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,830
the Tower Master asked
Second Prince for help,

231
00:11:47,030 --> 00:11:48,950
so why did she only open
a tiny rice ball shop?

232
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:50,600
Given how cunning she is,

233
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:52,750
it's impossible
she's only doing this to help

234
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:54,440
Yuanzhao make petty profits.

235
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:55,910
There must be

236
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:58,150
something fishy about this.

237
00:12:01,550 --> 00:12:02,670
Why isn't it my turn yet?

238
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:05,150
- Why aren't they selling yet?
- Yeah.

239
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:06,440
What's going on today?

240
00:12:06,450 --> 00:12:07,270
The customers are all here.

241
00:12:07,270 --> 00:12:08,140
Why aren't they selling yet?

242
00:12:08,150 --> 00:12:09,190
Tower Master, this is bad.

243
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:11,550
All the rice balls
in our kitchen are gone.

244
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,120
Where are my rice balls?

245
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,790
- Your Highness.
- Your Highness.

246
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:17,790
Your Highness,

247
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:20,870
my men and I have stolen back
all the rice balls from the shop.

248
00:12:23,790 --> 00:12:25,960
Rip every single one of them open
and check carefully.

249
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:28,320
See if there are any

250
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,080
secret notes

251
00:12:30,710 --> 00:12:31,720
or letters hidden inside.

252
00:12:37,510 --> 00:12:40,900
♪Snowflakes settle gently
upon your brows♪

253
00:12:41,660 --> 00:12:45,040
♪Your dark hair
brushes across my fingertips♪

254
00:12:45,810 --> 00:12:47,550
♪Your smile♪

255
00:12:47,810 --> 00:12:50,100
♪Melts away the winter snow♪

256
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:53,780
♪One fleeting glance says more
than a thousand words♪

257
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:57,550
♪Yet I stand before you♪

258
00:12:58,290 --> 00:13:02,120
♪Unable to recognize your eyes♪

259
00:13:02,540 --> 00:13:04,460
♪Though fate tries♪

260
00:13:04,460 --> 00:13:07,040
♪To make us pass each other by♪

261
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:10,680
♪I choose to make our story whole♪

262
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:12,570
♪Though time slips by♪

263
00:13:12,570 --> 00:13:14,330
♪As day turns into night♪

264
00:13:14,850 --> 00:13:18,870
♪I still remember
our days at Wangshi Tower♪

265
00:13:19,290 --> 00:13:21,670
♪One glance at you lasts a lifetime♪

266
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:23,460
♪Blessed by fate♪

267
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:28,620
♪I believe this moment
will last forever♪

268
00:13:28,620 --> 00:13:31,060
♪Your smiling face♪

269
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:33,900
♪Is the most beautiful poem♪

270
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:37,520
♪I'd rather spend my days with you♪

271
00:13:38,040 --> 00:13:41,500
♪And wander the world together♪

272
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:42,840
♪Holding you close♪

273
